techmeme.title: Germany's Munich Re agrees to acquire digital insurance company Next Insurance for $2.6B; Next Insurance has raised ~$1.2B from Capital G, Redpoint, and others (Mary Ann Azevedo/TechCrunch)
Source: Insight Partners is set to reap ~$2.7B from the pending sale of Wiz to Alphabet, a 15.5x return on its invested capital, based on its ~8% stake in Wiz (Gillian Tan/Bloomberg)
Anthropic adds web search in preview for Claude 3.7 Sonnet, available now for paid US Claude users, with support for free users and more countries coming soon (Kyle Wiggers/TechCrunch)
Source: Perplexity has discussed raising as much as $500M to $1B in a new round that would double its valuation to $18B; its current ARR is nearly $100M (Shirin Ghaffary/Bloomberg)
Threads rolls out new features: ability to set following feed or any custom feed as the default, limit post replies to followers, a better video player, more (Tom Warren/The Verge)
